            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="nar.03435.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
           
            <ab>Nov. 1, 1871.</ab>
            <ab>Hon. Hamilton Fish,</ab>
            <ab>Secretary of State.</ab>
            <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>Your letter of the 28th ultimo to the Acting Attorney General, enclosing the copy of a letter to you from Mr. C. W. Wessen, of Florence, Ala., has been received, and a communication has been addressed from this Department to Mr. Wessen on the subject of his letter.</ab>
            <ab>Very respectfully, &amp;c.</ab>
            <ab>A. T. Akerman,</ab>
            <ab>Attorney General.</ab>
            
            <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">C. W. Wessen, Ala.</note>
            
            
            
        </body>
